==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Remittitur
<hw>Re*mit"ti*tur</hw> <pr>(-t?-t?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.,
(it) is remitted.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A remission
or surrender, -- <stype>remittitur damnut</stype> being a remission of
excess of damages.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A sending back, as when a
record is remitted by a superior to an inferior court.</def>
<rj><au>Wharton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Remittor</ent>⟦br⟧
